00:14:24,785 --> 00:14:26,661
Did you investigate
that one, too?

261
00:14:26,738 --> 00:14:27,990
Oh, yeah.

262
00:14:28,065 --> 00:14:29,860
Figured that one out
in about a half-hour.

263
00:14:29,936 --> 00:14:30,862
Arson?

264
00:14:30,937 --> 00:14:32,202
In a big way.

265
00:14:32,265 --> 00:14:33,332
How can you tell?

266
00:14:33,405 --> 00:14:34,792
Tons of ways.

267
00:14:34,865 --> 00:14:36,133
You look
for accelerants,

268
00:14:36,207 --> 00:14:38,530
pour patterns,
ignition sources.

269
00:14:38,606 --> 00:14:40,232
But the surest way
to know is when you find

270
00:14:40,306 --> 00:14:42,231
the arsonist's
body right where
the fire started.

271
00:14:42,307 --> 00:14:43,561
Pretty much a slam dunk.

272
00:14:44,527 --> 00:14:46,270
Someone died in that fire?

273
00:14:46,288 --> 00:14:47,282
Co-owner.

274
00:14:47,347 --> 00:14:49,682
Tried to screw
his ex-partner over.

275
00:14:49,745 --> 00:14:51,443
Insurance scam
is what we figured.

276
00:14:51,515 --> 00:14:53,081
See it all the time.

277
00:14:53,147 --> 00:14:55,442
It's amazing
what people try
to get away with.

278
00:14:55,517 --> 00:14:57,713
Not too smart, though.

279
00:14:57,788 --> 00:14:59,740
Guy burned to death.

280
00:14:59,818 --> 00:15:02,942
People have
no idea how fast
a fire can spread.

281
00:15:02,946 --> 00:15:03,942
What about this fire?

282
00:15:04,045 --> 00:15:05,780
Any idea what caused it?

283
00:15:05,845 --> 00:15:08,043
This matters to you, why?

284
00:15:08,118 --> 00:15:10,943
Sorry. I'm just doing some
research on arson, fire,

285
00:15:11,018 --> 00:15:12,283
things like that.

286
00:15:12,347 --> 00:15:14,283
Mmm. You mean,
for a book or something?

287
00:15:14,348 --> 00:15:16,012
You never can tell.

288
00:15:16,087 --> 00:15:18,541
I haven't found
any evidence
to suggest arson.

289
00:15:18,616 --> 00:15:21,442
We're gonna keep
looking though.

290
00:15:21,515 --> 00:15:23,283
Say hi to jim
for me.

291
00:15:23,346 --> 00:15:24,611
Watch your step
on the way out.

292
00:15:24,688 --> 00:15:25,683
Thanks.

293
00:16:00,317 --> 00:16:01,682
Lilly chen.

294
00:16:14,545 --> 00:16:16,142
Lilly.

295
00:16:17,605 --> 00:16:18,302
What is that?

296
00:16:18,308 --> 00:16:19,380
Stained glass?

297
00:16:19,388 --> 00:16:20,583
Everything will burn.

298
00:16:22,146 --> 00:16:24,002
Everyone will burn.

299
00:16:24,077 --> 00:16:25,441
Yeah.

300
00:16:28,626 --> 00:16:29,722
I'm fine.

301
00:16:29,796 --> 00:16:32,290
I just got so hot
i couldn't breathe.

302
00:16:32,365 --> 00:16:34,792
I can't decide whether
to move into the firehouse

303
00:16:34,795 --> 00:16:36,101
or have the firehouse
move in here.

304
00:16:36,108 --> 00:16:38,673
Well, at least i know
who the ghost is.

305
00:16:38,676 --> 00:16:40,771
It's the guy who set
fire to his own restaurant?

306
00:16:40,777 --> 00:16:41,290
Yes.

307
00:16:41,306 --> 00:16:43,763
And then a year later
set fire to it again,
after he died?

308
00:16:43,766 --> 00:16:45,061
I think so.
Why?

309
00:16:45,128 --> 00:16:48,020
Maybe... i don't know.

310
00:16:48,025 --> 00:16:51,193
Maybe he's been
in some kind of sleep
state all this time.

311
00:16:51,266 --> 00:16:54,961
You know, it does
usually take some
big event or...

312
00:16:55,028 --> 00:16:57,121
i don't know,
some kind of ripple.

313
00:16:57,195 --> 00:17:00,820
And you think the re-opening
of the restaurant set him off?

314
00:17:00,827 --> 00:17:02,261
Well, yeah!

315
00:17:03,368 --> 00:17:04,721
I need you to lie down.

316
00:17:06,465 --> 00:17:07,662
That's not lying down.

317
00:17:07,728 --> 00:17:09,260
Well, why don't you
turn your head sideways,

318
00:17:09,326 --> 00:17:11,121
and then it'll look
like i'm lying down?

319
00:17:12,198 --> 00:17:13,423
You are a terrible patient.

320
00:17:13,497 --> 00:17:16,891
He said that everything
was going to burn.

321
00:17:16,965 --> 00:17:18,121
Every one
was going to burn.

322
00:17:18,197 --> 00:17:19,760
What for?
I don't know.

323
00:17:19,826 --> 00:17:22,223
But, you know,
he's obviously coming
to me for some reason.

324
00:17:22,228 --> 00:17:23,310
Maybe he wants my help.

325
00:17:23,316 --> 00:17:25,211
And maybe he's
just completely evil,

326
00:17:25,215 --> 00:17:26,261
and he enjoys the attention.

327
00:17:26,327 --> 00:17:27,821
Either way i have
to cross him over

328
00:17:27,898 --> 00:17:29,493
before he burns
something else down.

329
00:17:30,506 --> 00:17:32,092
All right.

330
00:17:32,167 --> 00:17:35,732
You said
he recognized his wife?

331
00:17:35,798 --> 00:17:36,931
Yeah, he said her name.

332
00:17:36,938 --> 00:17:38,433
I tried to find her
before you got home,

333
00:17:38,496 --> 00:17:39,931
and there's no listing
for her anywhere.

334
00:17:39,935 --> 00:17:41,462
Why don't you talk
to that guy jesse
at the restaurant?

335
00:17:41,537 --> 00:17:43,330
He knows...
warren chen.

336
00:17:43,397 --> 00:17:44,902
Right. His partner.
Talk to him,

337
00:17:44,968 --> 00:17:46,160
see what he can tell you.

338
00:17:47,995 --> 00:17:49,930
Can you get me
his address?

339
00:17:49,935 --> 00:17:53,730
Well... that depends
what's in it for me.

340
00:17:57,808 --> 00:17:59,931
How's your
blood pressure?

341
00:18:00,005 --> 00:18:01,431
Elevated.

342
00:18:03,716 --> 00:18:04,642
Now lie down.

343
00:18:04,717 --> 00:18:05,983
Ok, i'll lie down.

344
00:18:08,545 --> 00:18:10,582
I hope you don't mind
if i keep working.

345
00:18:10,646 --> 00:18:12,840
I got to get
this place in shape.

346
00:18:12,918 --> 00:18:14,983
It's gotta go on
the market next week.

347
00:18:15,047 --> 00:18:17,643
I know that
this is a bad time
for you right now.

348
00:18:17,718 --> 00:18:19,581
Yeah. Well, that's
what happens when you lose

349
00:18:19,647 --> 00:18:21,313
a business twice
in one year.

350
00:18:21,386 --> 00:18:23,312
Wasn't there
any insurance?

351
00:18:23,387 --> 00:18:27,043
Yeah, but with the first one,
they didn't want to pay.

352
00:18:27,116 --> 00:18:29,310
Insurance companies
tend to frown on arson.

353
00:18:29,386 --> 00:18:32,311
Then i had to borrow money
from my father to rebuild,

354
00:18:32,387 --> 00:18:34,111
and no one wanted to insure
the new place.

355
00:18:34,188 --> 00:18:37,211
Look, i really appreciate
what your husband did for me,

356
00:18:37,216 --> 00:18:39,642
but i really don't
want to think about any
of this right now.

357
00:18:39,717 --> 00:18:44,243
I'd like to talk
about the first fire,
last year.

358
00:18:44,315 --> 00:18:45,513
And warren chen.

359
00:18:45,516 --> 00:18:47,483
Why  are you doing this?
What do you want from me?

360
00:18:47,546 --> 00:18:49,381
I'd just like
to know more about him.

361
00:18:51,115 --> 00:18:54,313
Warren was my partner,
and he was my friend.

362
00:18:54,387 --> 00:18:55,682
He burned down
your restaurant.

363
00:18:55,748 --> 00:18:58,283
And it broke my heart!
He was like a brother to me.

364
00:18:58,288 --> 00:19:00,440
Look, i don't know why he did
what he did that night.

365
00:19:00,518 --> 00:19:01,941
But you didn't know him,

366
00:19:02,016 --> 00:19:03,503
and you can't come here
and talk about him

367
00:19:03,505 --> 00:19:05,310
like he's some kind
of criminal.

368
00:19:05,388 --> 00:19:07,443
Ok, i'm sorry.

369
00:19:07,515 --> 00:19:10,040
Ok. Well, now
i have things to do.

370
00:19:10,115 --> 00:19:12,341
What about lilly?

371
00:19:12,417 --> 00:19:13,501
Do you know
where she is?

372
00:19:13,507 --> 00:19:15,501
She had a total
breakdown after warren.

373
00:19:15,505 --> 00:19:18,513
Look, what do you want
from her and what do you
want from me?

374
00:19:18,587 --> 00:19:20,311
I'm sorry.

375
00:19:20,387 --> 00:19:21,502
I didn't mean to...

376
00:19:21,508 --> 00:19:23,010
just leave us alone.
Leave me alone.

377
00:19:23,088 --> 00:19:25,842
Leave her alone.
We've l been through enough.

378
00:19:28,187 --> 00:19:31,880
I really hate being
the only one who knows
how that fire got started.

379
00:19:31,947 --> 00:19:34,043
So, did jesse
say anything helpful?

380
00:19:34,116 --> 00:19:35,643
No. He's pretty raw.

381
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:37,481
I'm guess i'm going
to have to find lilly

382
00:19:37,546 --> 00:19:39,012
and see if she knows
anything that can help.

383
00:19:39,088 --> 00:19:39,751
Well, how are you going
to do that?

384
00:19:39,767 --> 00:19:41,710
You said there
was no listing.

385
00:19:41,787 --> 00:19:42,582
You can help me.

386
00:19:42,587 --> 00:19:43,741
I knew that was coming.

387
00:19:43,747 --> 00:19:45,141
Ok. All you have
to do is find out

388
00:19:45,217 --> 00:19:46,242
where she lived
with warren.

389
00:19:46,247 --> 00:19:48,112
I'm sure
there's a record
from the last fire.

390
00:19:48,186 --> 00:19:49,683
She might
still be there.

391
00:19:49,745 --> 00:19:51,181
I'll take a look.

392
00:19:51,248 --> 00:19:52,180
Ok.

393
00:19:52,248 --> 00:19:53,183
One kiss.

394
00:19:53,248 --> 00:19:54,413
Go to work.

395
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:06,211
They're gonna take a look.

396
00:20:06,286 --> 00:20:09,312
Don't worry.

397
00:20:12,288 --> 00:20:13,482
Let's go, let's go.

398
00:20:13,546 --> 00:20:15,183
There's somebody
still here.

399
00:20:19,515 --> 00:20:20,110
You ok?

400
00:20:20,117 --> 00:20:21,040
I'm all right.

401
00:20:21,115 --> 00:20:22,112
Let's do this.

402
00:20:23,446 --> 00:20:24,610
Anybody here?!

403
00:20:24,686 --> 00:20:25,782
Can you hear us?

404
00:20:25,847 --> 00:20:27,743
If you can hear us,
make a sound!

405
00:20:28,816 --> 00:20:30,041
Did you hear that?
What's that?

406
00:20:31,118 --> 00:20:32,242
Man: Get out!

407
00:20:32,315 --> 00:20:34,203
I hear something.
I think someone's here.

408
00:20:34,816 --> 00:20:35,723
Turn off the radio.
Radios off.

409
00:20:41,795 --> 00:20:43,752
Right there.
That's it.

410
00:20:50,997 --> 00:20:52,091
We got 2!

411
00:20:52,157 --> 00:20:54,221
Radio: We got them!
We found them!

412
00:20:54,297 --> 00:20:56,121
Move it!
Let's go!

413
00:21:38,757 --> 00:21:41,521
Make sure you
check on him, ok?

414
00:21:41,527 --> 00:21:42,791
Make sure he's ok?

415
00:21:43,155 --> 00:21:44,991
I will.

416
00:21:45,055 --> 00:21:46,222
Thank you.

417
00:22:42,028 --> 00:22:44,493
Hey, i'm going
across to lentos
on the square.

418
00:22:44,508 --> 00:22:45,141
You want anything?

419
00:22:45,147 --> 00:22:46,073
No, thanks.

420
00:22:46,147 --> 00:22:47,142
Whatcha looking up?

421
00:22:47,205 --> 00:22:48,673
Trying to find someone.

422
00:22:48,745 --> 00:22:50,471
Aren't we all?
Old friend?

423
00:22:50,545 --> 00:22:51,640
Not really.

424
00:22:51,717 --> 00:22:52,872
Old enemy?

425
00:22:52,948 --> 00:22:55,443
It's a long story.

426
00:22:55,515 --> 00:22:57,373
I'm starting
to get the idea

427
00:22:57,445 --> 00:23:00,142
that there's
a lot of long stories
attached to you.

428
00:23:00,208 --> 00:23:02,143
More than you know.

429
00:23:02,208 --> 00:23:03,803
Hey, it's cool,
i was just gonna...

430
00:23:03,878 --> 00:23:06,001
you know, it's a friend
of mine whose husband died,

431
00:23:06,078 --> 00:23:07,710
and i'm trying
to check up on her,

432
00:23:07,778 --> 00:23:09,513
but i don't
know how to find her.

433
00:23:09,578 --> 00:23:11,002
Phone book?

434
00:23:11,077 --> 00:23:12,943
No, i tried
the old number and it just
said disconnected.

435
00:23:13,007 --> 00:23:16,070
Hmm. You know,
i love those kind
of good puzzles.

436
00:23:16,145 --> 00:23:18,102
Yeah. I'll figure
this one out.

437
00:23:18,175 --> 00:23:22,342
So, has jim remembered
your anniversary yet?

438
00:23:22,415 --> 00:23:25,773
No. He's still playing
poker on friday night.

439
00:23:26,808 --> 00:23:28,373
Time for a hint?

440
00:23:29,505 --> 00:23:31,331
I don't want to trick him
into remembering.

441
00:23:31,336 --> 00:23:35,331
You know, men have so
much crap on their minds
this time of year.

442
00:23:35,408 --> 00:23:38,101
There's football,
basketball,
ice hockey...

443
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:40,301
<i>america's
next top model.</i>

444
00:23:41,505 --> 00:23:43,903
Yeah. I guess
it's no big deal.

445
00:23:43,968 --> 00:23:47,862
I mean, maybe
this stuff isn't that
important after all.

446
00:23:47,938 --> 00:23:50,600
Yeah, my husband
was really excellent

447
00:23:50,666 --> 00:23:53,033
at forgetting
our anniversary, too.

448
00:23:53,107 --> 00:23:55,532
And it didn't really
matter that much,

449
00:23:55,606 --> 00:23:57,900
or at least that's
what i told myself.

450
00:23:57,967 --> 00:24:00,030
And i would drop hints
all the time,

451
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:01,961
but it never worked.

452
00:24:02,038 --> 00:24:04,403
And finally one day
i just looked at him
and i said,

453
00:24:04,468 --> 00:24:08,300
charlie,
what the hell is it
about our anniversary?

454
00:24:08,365 --> 00:24:10,731
Why won't you
just remember it and
get it over with?

455
00:24:10,805 --> 00:24:13,831
And he looked
at me and he smiled,

456
00:24:13,905 --> 00:24:15,402
and he said...

457
00:24:15,467 --> 00:24:18,163
'cause
it's just one day.

458
00:24:18,238 --> 00:24:22,733
What's one day
when you compared it...

459
00:24:22,805 --> 00:24:25,901
to being married to you
every single day?

460
00:24:29,866 --> 00:24:31,261
That's a really good answer.

461
00:24:31,336 --> 00:24:34,500
Yeah. That was charlie.

462
00:24:42,138 --> 00:24:43,533
The funeral home.

463
00:24:43,606 --> 00:24:44,531
Sorry?

464
00:24:44,608 --> 00:24:45,732
Your friend.

465
00:24:45,806 --> 00:24:47,733
Why don't you check
with the funeral home

466
00:24:47,807 --> 00:24:49,262
where her husband
had his wake?

467
00:24:49,335 --> 00:24:52,361
What if she moved,
you know, after the wake?

468
00:24:52,437 --> 00:24:54,832
I bet they have
a cell number

469
00:24:54,836 --> 00:24:56,201
or maybe
her work number.

470
00:24:56,268 --> 00:24:57,950
You are a genius.

471
00:24:57,958 --> 00:24:58,531
Right.

472
00:24:58,605 --> 00:25:00,460
Please tell my son that.

473
00:25:01,007 --> 00:25:01,963
Bye.

474
00:25:02,038 --> 00:25:03,663
Bye.

475
00:25:19,136 --> 00:25:21,303
The chens.

476
00:25:21,365 --> 00:25:24,232
I remember the chen family.

477
00:25:24,235 --> 00:25:25,393
Do you remember
the wife?

478
00:25:25,395 --> 00:25:26,433
Lilly?

479
00:25:26,496 --> 00:25:28,431
Just that she seemed so sad.

480
00:25:28,498 --> 00:25:32,260
It was only her and a man,
about her age...

481
00:25:32,335 --> 00:25:35,061
he was just inconsolable.

482
00:25:35,138 --> 00:25:37,361
Cried more than she did,
if i remember.

483
00:25:37,436 --> 00:25:39,493
Must have been jesse,
his partner.

484
00:25:39,568 --> 00:25:40,733
I didn't get the name.

485
00:25:40,797 --> 00:25:42,061
I tried to comfort them,

486
00:25:42,138 --> 00:25:44,861
tried to tell them that
warren was at peace now...

487
00:25:44,935 --> 00:25:48,230
but, of course...

488
00:25:48,295 --> 00:25:49,563
i know.

489
00:25:49,637 --> 00:25:51,390
So sorry
to keep you waiting.

490
00:25:51,466 --> 00:25:53,432
We do still have the records
from that funeral,

491
00:25:53,498 --> 00:25:57,220
but i'm afraid
i couldn't give you any
personal information.

492
00:25:57,225 --> 00:25:58,062
Oh, i understand.

493
00:25:58,136 --> 00:26:01,732
But if i could
impose on you just
a little bit more...

494
00:26:01,796 --> 00:26:03,990
um, would you mind
calling ms. Chen

495
00:26:04,067 --> 00:26:06,192
and just giving her
my phone number,

496
00:26:06,268 --> 00:26:08,863
just let her know
that i have a message
about warren,

497
00:26:08,938 --> 00:26:10,830
and that it's
really important
that i speak to her.

498
00:26:10,898 --> 00:26:11,931
If it's that important...

499
00:26:11,995 --> 00:26:13,832
thanks, i really
appreciate that.

500
00:26:13,896 --> 00:26:16,192
Tell him he did
a fantastic job on the hair

501
00:26:16,267 --> 00:26:17,693
for the woman in room 5.

502
00:26:17,765 --> 00:26:19,331
The family loved it.

503
00:26:19,396 --> 00:26:21,393
So did she.

504
00:26:22,838 --> 00:26:24,730
People really
love your work.

505
00:26:36,668 --> 00:26:38,093
Let's walk.

506
00:26:38,166 --> 00:26:42,132
I have to admit,
i didn't think
you'd call me back.

507
00:26:42,195 --> 00:26:44,163
I'm not sure why i did.

508
00:26:44,235 --> 00:26:46,433
But for some reason
i felt like i had to.

509
00:26:47,698 --> 00:26:49,562
You said you had a message
about warren.

510
00:26:50,505 --> 00:26:51,242
Did you know him?

511
00:26:51,245 --> 00:26:53,060
No, not really. Um...

512
00:26:53,138 --> 00:26:55,460
i've been doing
some research on
the restaurant fire,

513
00:26:55,536 --> 00:26:57,033
the red noir.

514
00:26:57,098 --> 00:26:58,491
You know,
i don't mean to pry,

515
00:26:58,506 --> 00:27:01,393
but do you know
why warren would
do what he did?

516
00:27:01,468 --> 00:27:03,762
It doesn't make sense.

