00:27:03,836 --> 00:27:05,762
What was he like?

518
00:27:05,838 --> 00:27:08,860
He always said his life
had perfect balance,

519
00:27:08,938 --> 00:27:12,260
except then he got
into business with jesse.

520
00:27:12,338 --> 00:27:13,590
To be his partner.

521
00:27:13,668 --> 00:27:15,591
Yes, and that
was the problem.

522
00:27:15,666 --> 00:27:17,132
He wasn't just
a chef anymore.

523
00:27:17,198 --> 00:27:18,661
He had to deal
with the business...

524
00:27:18,735 --> 00:27:20,793
the hiring, the firing.

525
00:27:20,865 --> 00:27:24,230
He hated it.
Worst of all,

526
00:27:24,295 --> 00:27:26,030
it had nothing
to do with his talent,

527
00:27:26,095 --> 00:27:28,531
what made him happy.

528
00:27:28,595 --> 00:27:30,493
His mood changed.

529
00:27:30,566 --> 00:27:33,332
He was always
so stressed.

530
00:27:33,396 --> 00:27:35,091
Do you think that's
why he set the fire?

531
00:27:35,168 --> 00:27:36,962
So he could
get out of it?

532
00:27:37,037 --> 00:27:38,632
I just don't know.

533
00:27:38,698 --> 00:27:42,632
What if i told you
there was a way you
could ask him?

534
00:27:42,695 --> 00:27:44,923
I don't know what you...

535
00:27:44,938 --> 00:27:48,191
what if i said
that warren's spirit
is still here?

536
00:27:50,437 --> 00:27:54,462
I can help you talk
to him, through me.

537
00:27:57,097 --> 00:27:59,831
No. Lilly, please...

538
00:27:59,896 --> 00:28:01,791
he showed me
a piece of glass.

539
00:28:01,867 --> 00:28:04,260
Stained glass, does that
mean anything to you?

540
00:28:06,465 --> 00:28:07,992
I don't want him to see me.

541
00:28:09,667 --> 00:28:11,792
??????????

542
00:28:19,337 --> 00:28:20,331
Warren?

543
00:28:22,498 --> 00:28:24,231
Warren chen?

544
00:28:24,296 --> 00:28:26,933
I need to talk to you.

545
00:28:26,996 --> 00:28:29,361
I can help you.

546
00:28:29,438 --> 00:28:32,763
I spoke to your wife
and jesse.

547
00:28:32,838 --> 00:28:36,763
They don't really
understand why you
did what you did.

548
00:28:36,835 --> 00:28:37,832
Warren:
What did i do?

549
00:28:40,366 --> 00:28:42,933
Set the restaurant
on fire. Twice.

550
00:28:42,995 --> 00:28:44,162
Don't you remember that?

551
00:28:44,237 --> 00:28:45,661
I remember being mad
at jesse.

552
00:28:46,545 --> 00:28:47,491
Why?

553
00:28:47,505 --> 00:28:48,731
I wanted him to buy me out.

554
00:28:48,807 --> 00:28:50,702
I needed him to buy me out.

555
00:28:50,766 --> 00:28:52,062
He kept telling me
he'd pay me off,

556
00:28:52,138 --> 00:28:53,173
and then he'd always
have an excuse.

557
00:28:53,178 --> 00:28:54,741
He was never going
to give me what was mine.

558
00:28:54,808 --> 00:28:57,270
Did you think you
were going to get money
from the fire?

559
00:28:57,346 --> 00:29:00,240
From the insurance?
Or were you just trying
to get back at jesse?

560
00:29:00,256 --> 00:29:01,270
I don't remember.

561
00:29:03,035 --> 00:29:05,733
You really hate
this place.

562
00:29:05,738 --> 00:29:08,200
I was a chef...

563
00:29:08,275 --> 00:29:09,803
before.

564
00:29:09,877 --> 00:29:11,291
I used to love
to come to work.

565
00:29:11,307 --> 00:29:12,360
I couldn't wait.

566
00:29:12,438 --> 00:29:14,430
People loved what i did.

567
00:29:14,508 --> 00:29:15,492
When i got this place
with jesse,

568
00:29:15,505 --> 00:29:16,560
it all changed.

569
00:29:17,105 --> 00:29:20,330
I used to dream
about fire...

570
00:29:21,666 --> 00:29:24,003
about this place
burning down.

571
00:29:25,338 --> 00:29:26,862
And then i'd be free.

572
00:29:31,466 --> 00:29:32,901
Warren, i know how
much pain you're in,

573
00:29:32,967 --> 00:29:35,003
but you have to cross over.
There's a better place for you.

574
00:29:35,006 --> 00:29:36,503
I can't.

575
00:29:39,337 --> 00:29:42,331
Ok. Look, the revenge
that you wanted to get
on jesse, you got it.

576
00:29:42,408 --> 00:29:43,660
All right? He's ruined.

577
00:29:43,736 --> 00:29:45,362
He's probably
never going to be able

578
00:29:45,436 --> 00:29:46,430
to open a business again.

579
00:29:46,508 --> 00:29:47,830
It's lilly.

580
00:29:49,838 --> 00:29:51,562
There's something
she has to know.

581
00:29:51,635 --> 00:29:52,860
What?

582
00:29:56,538 --> 00:29:58,062
I don't know.

583
00:29:58,137 --> 00:30:00,132
Does it have something to do
with that stained glass?

584
00:30:01,366 --> 00:30:03,533
I love her so much.

585
00:30:08,367 --> 00:30:10,203
I'm afraid i hurt her.

586
00:30:12,668 --> 00:30:14,530
I have to talk to her.

587
00:30:18,208 --> 00:30:20,432
Don't let lilly think
i forgot her.

588
00:30:50,407 --> 00:30:51,600
You know what, noah?

589
00:30:51,667 --> 00:30:54,462
I think i'll see you
back at the station.

590
00:30:59,006 --> 00:31:00,103
Ah!
Sorry...

591
00:31:00,165 --> 00:31:02,030
aah!
It's ok.

592
00:31:04,538 --> 00:31:05,530
You remember me?

593
00:31:05,607 --> 00:31:08,501
Yeah. You threw
my slipper at me.

594
00:31:08,568 --> 00:31:09,932
Tossed.

595
00:31:10,006 --> 00:31:11,490
I tossed it at you.
There's a difference.

596
00:31:11,505 --> 00:31:12,490
Let me see
if i can fix this.

597
00:31:12,507 --> 00:31:13,493
There's a trick to it.

598
00:31:13,507 --> 00:31:14,632
Yeah.

599
00:31:16,505 --> 00:31:17,552
That's not it.

600
00:31:17,558 --> 00:31:20,222
I hope you're better
at putting out fires.

601
00:31:20,295 --> 00:31:21,691
I'll buy you a new one.

602
00:31:21,757 --> 00:31:23,251
Don't worry about it.

603
00:31:23,325 --> 00:31:26,103
I'm jim...
jim clancy,
by the way.

604
00:31:26,106 --> 00:31:26,652
Melinda gordon.

605
00:31:26,725 --> 00:31:27,651
Nice to meet you.

606
00:31:27,726 --> 00:31:28,851
I have to...

607
00:31:28,926 --> 00:31:30,022
where you headed?

608
00:31:30,098 --> 00:31:34,023
Uh... now
to get an umbrella.

609
00:31:34,096 --> 00:31:35,350
Right.

610
00:31:35,427 --> 00:31:38,451
Produce. My apartment
is full of soot, so...

611
00:31:38,526 --> 00:31:40,750
i don't know about you,
but i'm starved.

612
00:31:40,828 --> 00:31:42,120
Well, good luck
with that.

613
00:31:42,198 --> 00:31:45,053
Hey, let me buy you
a late dinner.

614
00:31:45,128 --> 00:31:46,452
I know a place.

615
00:31:46,528 --> 00:31:48,123
What place?

616
00:31:50,126 --> 00:31:51,890
Ever heard
of the umbrella room?

617
00:31:51,957 --> 00:31:53,352
No.

618
00:31:53,426 --> 00:31:54,352
Come on.

619
00:31:58,307 --> 00:31:59,681
?????????

620
00:32:00,856 --> 00:32:02,551
Well, you got class,
i'll give you that.

621
00:32:02,628 --> 00:32:04,652
Anybody can take
you to sardi's.

622
00:32:04,727 --> 00:32:06,052
Thanks, boss.

623
00:32:06,128 --> 00:32:08,252
You won't find
this kind of food there.

624
00:32:08,328 --> 00:32:09,892
One can hope.

625
00:32:14,128 --> 00:32:15,650
Do you live close by?

626
00:32:16,727 --> 00:32:19,723
Well, near.
West 90th.

627
00:32:20,897 --> 00:32:22,293
That's the upper west side.

628
00:32:22,357 --> 00:32:23,993
This is the east village.

629
00:32:24,056 --> 00:32:25,753
That's not close at all.

630
00:32:25,826 --> 00:32:28,353
I was never any good
with a compass.

631
00:32:31,025 --> 00:32:34,691
You got a little, uh...

632
00:32:35,928 --> 00:32:37,253
on your lip.

633
00:32:43,558 --> 00:32:44,791
What?

634
00:32:44,857 --> 00:32:46,321
Nothing.

635
00:32:48,016 --> 00:32:48,792
I know.

636
00:32:48,856 --> 00:32:51,291
You were pretty
sure that guy was
in that apartment.

637
00:32:51,357 --> 00:32:52,822
Lucky guess.

638
00:32:52,895 --> 00:32:54,250
No. You knew.

639
00:32:54,328 --> 00:32:55,392
You were sure.

640
00:32:55,456 --> 00:32:57,023
I've been thinking
about it all night.

641
00:32:57,027 --> 00:32:58,023
How did you know?

642
00:32:58,096 --> 00:32:59,793
You know what?
I have to go home.

643
00:32:59,856 --> 00:33:00,952
I have work in the morning.

644
00:33:01,026 --> 00:33:02,792
You know,
i hate secrets.

645
00:33:02,855 --> 00:33:05,021
So, how did you know?

646
00:33:12,898 --> 00:33:14,820
Maybe someday
i'll tell you.

647
00:33:26,356 --> 00:33:27,823
Earth to melinda.

648
00:33:27,897 --> 00:33:29,091
Sorry.

649
00:33:29,157 --> 00:33:31,221
I was lost in thought.

650
00:33:31,296 --> 00:33:32,621
What about?

651
00:33:32,696 --> 00:33:35,752
Um... about...

652
00:33:35,826 --> 00:33:39,921
about how to get lilly chen
to talk to her husband.

653
00:33:39,996 --> 00:33:43,221
I never got her number
when she met me.

654
00:33:43,296 --> 00:33:44,623
But she called you, right?

655
00:33:44,696 --> 00:33:46,621
So it's probably
in my phone memory.
Hello.

656
00:33:46,695 --> 00:33:49,120
Uh. Here. Look.

657
00:33:49,195 --> 00:33:51,350
This number...
i don't recognize it.

658
00:33:51,428 --> 00:33:53,451
That's got to be it.

659
00:33:53,525 --> 00:33:54,992
So?

660
00:33:55,056 --> 00:33:57,592
I just don't like
doing this kind of thing
over the phone.

661
00:33:57,657 --> 00:34:00,521
You mean you really
don't like the hanging-up-
in-your-face part.

662
00:34:00,597 --> 00:34:02,723
Exactly.

663
00:34:02,795 --> 00:34:03,751
You online?

664
00:34:03,828 --> 00:34:05,091
Yeah...

665
00:34:05,158 --> 00:34:06,090
let me try something.

666
00:34:07,797 --> 00:34:10,351
All right.
This is a reverse
phone directory site.

667
00:34:10,427 --> 00:34:11,790
You put
the phone number in,

668
00:34:11,857 --> 00:34:13,793
you get
an address, unless
it's been blocked.

669
00:34:13,856 --> 00:34:15,021
You never cease to amaze me.

670
00:34:15,095 --> 00:34:16,723
Ditto.

671
00:34:25,457 --> 00:34:26,791
What?

672
00:34:26,855 --> 00:34:30,850
You already
gave me this address.

673
00:35:06,506 --> 00:35:08,333
There was a time
he was like my brother.

674
00:35:10,705 --> 00:35:12,462
I'm so sorry, warren.

675
00:35:12,535 --> 00:35:13,562
And lilly...

676
00:35:15,535 --> 00:35:17,500
she was my wife.

677
00:35:17,568 --> 00:35:19,560
We went through
so much together.

678
00:35:19,565 --> 00:35:21,502
Look, we don't really
know what happened...

679
00:35:21,507 --> 00:35:22,492
or when it happened.

680
00:35:22,507 --> 00:35:23,491
I just died.
How could they...

681
00:35:23,507 --> 00:35:25,230
you died a year ago, warren.

682
00:35:25,308 --> 00:35:27,162
Things change.

683
00:35:27,168 --> 00:35:29,502
People change. Sometimes
they have to move on.

684
00:35:29,506 --> 00:35:30,972
I'm going to burn them.

685
00:35:31,038 --> 00:35:32,233
No.

686
00:35:32,306 --> 00:35:35,003
I will burn everything.

687
00:35:47,975 --> 00:35:49,302
Jesse!

688
00:35:49,368 --> 00:35:50,502
Jesse!

689
00:35:52,668 --> 00:35:54,561
Ow! Jesse!

690
00:35:57,065 --> 00:35:58,030
Hey, what the hell is...

691
00:35:58,106 --> 00:35:59,431
god, it's hot.
Are you all right?

692
00:35:59,505 --> 00:36:01,160
It's just my furnace.
What's wrong with you?

693
00:36:01,238 --> 00:36:03,160
There is nothing wrong
with your furnace.

694
00:36:03,237 --> 00:36:04,433
Ok? Just please
come outside?

695
00:36:04,505 --> 00:36:05,432
Why?

696
00:36:05,505 --> 00:36:06,931
Just please.
Warren's here.

697
00:36:07,006 --> 00:36:08,970
Warren? What are you
talking about?

698
00:36:09,037 --> 00:36:10,602
Warren's spirit
is still here.

699
00:36:10,666 --> 00:36:12,263
Ok? He's been haunting
the restaurant.

700
00:36:12,336 --> 00:36:13,762
He caused the fire.
And he knows about
you and lilly,

701
00:36:13,768 --> 00:36:15,162
and he's really mad...

702
00:36:15,237 --> 00:36:16,162
are you on drugs?

703
00:36:16,236 --> 00:36:18,002
Warren, don't do this!

704
00:36:25,838 --> 00:36:26,700
What the hell?

705
00:36:26,707 --> 00:36:29,463
She says warren's
spirit is still here.

706
00:36:29,535 --> 00:36:30,972
Look, he knows
about you and jesse.

707
00:36:31,037 --> 00:36:32,032
You have to talk to him

708
00:36:32,108 --> 00:36:33,631
before he burns
the house down.

709
00:36:34,977 --> 00:36:35,902
Are you ok?

710
00:36:35,977 --> 00:36:38,733
Aah! Please!

711
00:36:38,806 --> 00:36:41,263
If that's you,
if you're doing this,

712
00:36:41,337 --> 00:36:43,903
please stop!
I'm so sorry!

713
00:36:43,976 --> 00:36:46,181
Tell him how much
you love him.

714
00:36:46,186 --> 00:36:48,432
Use his name.

715
00:36:50,465 --> 00:36:51,763
Warren!

716
00:36:51,836 --> 00:36:54,600
I love you so much!

717
00:36:54,667 --> 00:36:56,903
He's right here...

718
00:36:56,976 --> 00:36:59,332
next to me.

719
00:37:03,836 --> 00:37:05,830
Ask her how long.

720
00:37:05,906 --> 00:37:07,362
How long was she with him?

721
00:37:07,435 --> 00:37:08,870
Before i died?

722
00:37:08,935 --> 00:37:10,062
He wants to know

723
00:37:10,067 --> 00:37:12,460
if you were with jesse
before he died.

724
00:37:12,538 --> 00:37:13,660
No, never...

725
00:37:13,738 --> 00:37:14,870
it wasn't like that.

726
00:37:14,935 --> 00:37:16,232
Warren...

727
00:37:16,306 --> 00:37:18,561
i knew you loved me.

728
00:37:21,507 --> 00:37:25,831
All i wanted was for us
to get our lives back...

729
00:37:25,837 --> 00:37:29,603
i wanted you to quit,
to be happy...

730
00:37:29,665 --> 00:37:32,533
i didn't mean for it
to happen, warren.

731
00:37:32,607 --> 00:37:35,631
I never thought
of jesse that way...

732
00:37:35,707 --> 00:37:38,631
but when you...

733
00:37:38,706 --> 00:37:41,301
when you died...

734
00:37:41,365 --> 00:37:45,002
we were
both so... so lost.

735
00:37:46,467 --> 00:37:48,403
Jesse was destroyed.

736
00:37:48,465 --> 00:37:50,563
He cried for you...

737
00:37:50,637 --> 00:37:54,931
he called your name.
He was so torn up.

738
00:37:55,977 --> 00:37:57,432
Warren: No!

739
00:37:57,507 --> 00:37:59,433
He cried.

740
00:38:01,505 --> 00:38:03,002
Jesse.

741
00:38:04,668 --> 00:38:06,262
Now i remember.

742
00:38:06,337 --> 00:38:08,362
He remembers.

743
00:38:11,507 --> 00:38:15,131
Lilly was making
a stained glass window
for our bedroom.

744
00:38:15,207 --> 00:38:19,060
I saw this beautiful piece
of glass on my lunch hour.

745
00:38:19,135 --> 00:38:21,231
I hadn't bought her a gift
in such a long time.

746
00:38:21,307 --> 00:38:23,432
And i'd had another fight
with jesse about the money.

747
00:38:23,505 --> 00:38:24,930
I left work mad
and was halfway home

748
00:38:25,007 --> 00:38:26,732
when i realized
i forgot the gift.

749
00:38:26,805 --> 00:38:28,661
I went in the back way...

750
00:38:38,668 --> 00:38:40,002
jesse!

751
00:38:40,066 --> 00:38:41,870
What are you doing?

752
00:38:47,435 --> 00:38:48,762
He watched you.

753
00:38:48,836 --> 00:38:52,702
He watched you
set the fire.

754
00:38:57,368 --> 00:38:59,662
Is this true?

755
00:39:01,975 --> 00:39:03,902
Lilly, please.

756
00:39:05,335 --> 00:39:07,731
You have to believe me.
I didn't mean to.

757
00:39:13,505 --> 00:39:15,001
I did it for all of us!

758
00:39:15,006 --> 00:39:16,462
We were going broke!

759
00:39:16,535 --> 00:39:17,500
It wasn't working!

760
00:39:17,506 --> 00:39:19,491
And i thought
if warren found out,

761
00:39:19,507 --> 00:39:20,501
that he'd quit
for sure.

762
00:39:21,768 --> 00:39:24,561
The insurance paid off,
we'd just start over.

763
00:39:24,636 --> 00:39:26,100
Clean slate.

764
00:39:26,167 --> 00:39:27,760
I made one mistake.

765
00:39:27,836 --> 00:39:29,500
He wasn't supposed
to be there.

766
00:39:29,566 --> 00:39:32,063
I don't know why
warren came back.

767
00:39:35,207 --> 00:39:37,100
What the hell
are you doing here?
Get out!

768
00:39:38,537 --> 00:39:40,461
Go on! Go on!
Go back!

769
00:39:40,536 --> 00:39:41,462
I can't!

770
00:39:41,537 --> 00:39:42,460
Why'd you come back here?!

771
00:39:42,536 --> 00:39:43,790
Why did you do this?

772
00:39:43,868 --> 00:39:45,961
Warren, get out of here!
Go on! Come on!

773
00:39:46,035 --> 00:39:49,200
Make a run for it!
No! No, no, not there!

774
00:39:49,266 --> 00:39:50,762
Aah!
Not there!

775
00:39:50,838 --> 00:39:51,833
Aah!
No!

776
00:40:00,167 --> 00:40:03,060
I swear i didn't
mean to hurt him.

777
00:40:03,137 --> 00:40:05,033
Just let him
take the blame.

778
00:40:05,106 --> 00:40:06,933
Yeah, but what
difference did it make?

779
00:40:07,005 --> 00:40:08,861
Nothing could have
brought warren back.

780
00:40:08,938 --> 00:40:11,792
I never said he did it.

781
00:40:11,868 --> 00:40:14,230
The arson
investigators did.

782
00:40:17,636 --> 00:40:18,961
Lilly please...
uhh!

783
00:40:19,036 --> 00:40:20,302
Get away from me!

784
00:40:23,795 --> 00:40:26,243
It wasn't the reopening
